      • sd

        public final double sd
        This field contains the value that is called "accuracy" in Android APIs, but the name "accuracy" is confusing because a higher "accuracy" value actually represents lower accuracy. What does an "accuracy" of 6 even mean? In the Android documentation, this value is specified to be the radius, in meters, of a 68% confidence circle (i.e. one standard deviation from the mean); thus we use the more precise name "sd" for "standard deviation".
